                            <comment id="10492" author="robh" created="Mon, 21 Jun 2004 01:43:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The patch that has been made is on an old version of the CglibPoxy class. In the new CglibProxy class the Callbacks are &lt;b&gt;not&lt;/b&gt; the same for each proxy on the same superclass and will change based on the parameters (frozen, exposeProxy) as well as on the target source and the advice chain. This pattern will continue as I add support to Cglib for generating the bytecode specific to an advice chain. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So you need to key the cache on the Callbacks and the superclass not just the superclass. However, it is important to note that Cglib does in fact create all instances after the first using the Factory interface anyway and it already takes care of caching the proxy classes appropriately, so the benefit of maintaining a separate cache is negligible&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Rob&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="10493" author="tysonnorris" created="Mon, 21 Jun 2004 03:56:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Maybe I&apos;m taking the wrong approach - I&apos;m trying to avoid the callback filter method iteration. I assumed this was a problem with not caching the Enhancer Factory. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For example, with each bean instance, the log show CGLIB calling the callback filter to iterate the methods etc. It seems unnecessary to do this multiple times when the interceptor instances are singletons. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="10499" author="tysonnorris" created="Mon, 21 Jun 2004 08:10:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Also - I tried the latest revision of post-1.0.2 Cglib2AopProxy class. I saw the same problem where the callback filter still iterates all methods in the proxied instance with each instantiation.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="10546" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2004 23:33:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;What&apos;s the state of this? Has this issue been resolved?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="10552" author="tysonnorris" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2004 03:26:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue was fixed with Rob&apos;s latest changes to Cglib2AopProxy class.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="10564" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Thu, 1 Jul 2004 06:21:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Then let&apos;s consider it fixed &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
